Kebbi State chapters of Nigerian Union of Journalists (NUJ) and Nigerian Association of Women Journalists (NAWOJ),  have donated food items to families of the deceased members of NUJ and 200 vulnerable households to cushion the effect of harsh economy. Speaking during the distribution, the Chairman of NUJ, Aliyu Jajirma, said the donation was to cushion the effect of economic hardship they might be encountering. Jajirma thanked the wife of the state governor, Dr. Zainab Shinkafi Bagudu, and others for also donating to the families. “Over 17 families of the deceased members of NUJ received cash, clothing materials and food items. The intervention programme was conceived five years ago and since then, it has been consistent.” In same vein, the chairperson of NAWOJ, Mrs. Laiatu Augustine Bamaiyi, said with support from the Khadimiyya Foundation her association had distributed palliatives to 200 vulnerable households. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here According to her, NAWOJ reached out to the vulnerable people in Amanawa community, Mashekara and Bayan Kara communities.  NUJ donates relief materials, cash to 17 families of late journalists in Kebbi Gaidam mourns late VOA correspondent ‘Entrench affirmative action in the constitution’